00:00:00,138 --> 00:00:03,510
So, this is the general equation for any circle.

2
00:00:03,510 --> 00:00:05,555
The number on the end is "r" squared,

3
00:00:05,555 --> 00:00:08,828
and so the square root of this number is the radius.

4
00:00:08,828 --> 00:00:12,548
And then if there's a number next to the "x", and a number next to the "k",

5
00:00:12,548 --> 00:00:15,587
these are the numbers that form our center.

6
00:00:15,587 --> 00:00:19,385
We take their opposite sign from the one that's in parenthesis.

7
00:00:19,385 --> 00:00:25,029
So, for example, if this is negative and this is negative, then both "h" and "k" will be positive.

8
00:00:25,029 --> 00:00:28,092
Whereas if there were positive signs inside of our equations,

9
00:00:28,092 --> 00:00:31,206
that means that these two values would be negative.

10
00:00:31,206 --> 00:00:34,208
Let's check out a few examples to see this in action.

11
00:00:34,208 --> 00:00:38,346
Here's a circle centered at the origin with a radius of 5.

12
00:00:38,346 --> 00:00:42,526
Notice that this equation is really the same as this one.

13
00:00:42,526 --> 00:00:49,127
If we subtracted or added zero to the "x" and "y" value, we'd still be at a center of (0,0).

14
00:00:49,127 --> 00:00:52,402
This is our "h" and this is our "k".

15
