And it turns out that this is true for all the points on this circle.

25
00:01:42,176 --> 00:01:47,769
We can examine another point and see that it was moved three units right and then three units up.

26
00:01:47,769 --> 00:01:50,044
And here's a different circle.

27
00:01:50,044 --> 00:01:55,873
This one's been shifted four units to the left, and then one unit up, vertically.

28
00:01:55,873 --> 00:02:01,294
And notice, too, that the center of this new circle is at (-4,1).

29
00:02:01,294 --> 00:02:07,712
This is the "h" value and it's opposite in sign of the equation, and this is the "k" value

30
00:02:07,712 --> 00:02:10,340
which is opposite of this number in the equation.

